---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Child Custody Attorneys in Maryland | Parenting Plans & Best Interests Standard | Child Custody with a Plan"
  description="Maryland child custody attorneys for legal and physical custody, parenting plans, joint and sole custody disputes. Best-interests standard representation. Call (301) 289-8917."
  ogTitle="Maryland Child Custody Attorneys | Child Custody with a Plan"
  ogDescription="Strategic child custody representation in Maryland. Legal custody, physical custody, parenting plans, and the best-interests standard — handled with expertise and compassion."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative bg-[#0D6E6E] text-white py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10 bg-[url('/grid.svg')] bg-repeat"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <p class="text-[#D4A843] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-sm mb-3">Maryland Child Custody Law</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight mb-5">
        Child Custody Attorneys<br class="hidden md:block" /> Who Put Children First
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-white/80 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">
        Custody disputes are among the most emotionally charged legal matters a parent will ever face. We approach every case with strategic precision and deep compassion — always with your children's best interests at heart.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-[#D4A843] text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#b8902f] transition-colors">
          Book Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:3012898917" class="border-2 border-white text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-white hover:text-[#0D6E6E] transition-colors">
          (301) 289-8917
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Breadcrumb -->
  <div class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-3">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-[#0D6E6E]">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-gray-800 font-medium">Child Custody</span>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-5">Understanding Child Custody in Maryland</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Maryland courts decide all custody matters using one overriding standard: the <strong>best interests of the child</strong>. This standard guides every decision — from temporary orders during divorce proceedings to final custody orders and post-divorce modifications.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Maryland recognizes two distinct types of custody: <strong>legal custody</strong> (decision-making authority) and <strong>physical custody</strong> (where the child lives). Each type can be awarded solely to one parent or shared jointly — and these arrangements don't have to match.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600">
            A parent can have joint legal custody while the other parent has primary physical custody — or many other combinations. Our job is to understand your unique family situation and advocate for the arrangement that genuinely serves your children's wellbeing and your parental rights.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-[#0D6E6E] text-white rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">Maryland Custody at a Glance</h3>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
              <div>
                <p class="text-[#D4A843] font-bold mb-2">Legal Custody</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-white/85">
                  <li>• Decision-making authority</li>
                  <li>• Education choices</li>
                  <li>• Healthcare decisions</li>
                  <li>• Religious upbringing</li>
                  <li>• Extracurricular activities</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-[#D4A843] font-bold mb-2">Physical Custody</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-white/85">
                  <li>• Where child resides</li>
                  <li>• Day-to-day parenting</li>
                  <li>• Overnight schedules</li>
                  <li>• Holiday arrangements</li>
                  <li>• School-year vs. summer</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-[#D4A843]/30 rounded-xl p-5">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
              <strong class="text-[#D4A843]">Our certified edge:</strong> Our firm's attorneys include those certified as Best Interest Attorneys (BIA) — court-appointed advocates trained specifically to represent children's rights in Maryland family court.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Types of Custody -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-3">Types of Custody Arrangements in Maryland</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">No two families are the same. Maryland courts have broad discretion to craft custody arrangements that fit each family's specific circumstances.</p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            title: "Joint Legal Custody",
            icon: "🤝",
            color: "border-[#0D6E6E]",
            headerBg: "bg-[#0D6E6E]",
            desc: "Both parents share decision-making authority for major decisions affecting the child — education, healthcare, religious upbringing, and more.",
            when: "Most common arrangement in Maryland. Works best when parents can communicate and cooperate effectively.",
            note: "Even with joint legal custody, day-to-day decisions are made by whichever parent has the child at that time."
          },
          {
            title: "Sole Legal Custody",
            icon: "👤",
            color: "border-gray-500",
            headerBg: "bg-gray-700",
            desc: "One parent has exclusive authority to make major decisions for the child without the other parent's input or agreement.",
            when: "Awarded when parents cannot cooperate, one parent is uninvolved, or there is a history of domestic violence, abuse, or substance abuse.",
            note: "The non-custodial parent still typically has visitation rights unless circumstances justify supervised or restricted visitation."
          },
          {
            title: "Primary Physical Custody",
            icon: "🏠",
            color: "border-[#D4A843]",
            headerBg: "bg-[#D4A843]",
            desc: "The child lives primarily with one parent (the custodial parent), with the other parent having regular visitation time.",
            when: "Common when parents live in different school districts, children are very young, or one parent's schedule is substantially more available.",
            note: "Visitation for the non-custodial parent is a fundamental right and is strongly protected by Maryland courts."
          },
          {
            title: "Shared Physical Custody",
            icon: "↔️",
            color: "border-gray-300",
            headerBg: "bg-gray-600",
            desc: "The child spends substantial time with both parents — typically at least 35% overnight time with each parent. Does not have to be exactly 50/50.",
            when: "Works best when parents live near each other, can coordinate effectively, and both are actively involved in the child's daily life.",
            note: "Shared custody affects child support calculations under Maryland guidelines. We carefully model financial impacts."
          }
        ].map(type => (
          <div class={`bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border-l-4 ${type.color} overflow-hidden`}>
            <div class={`${type.headerBg} px-6 py-4 flex items-center gap-3`}>
              <span class="text-2xl">{type.icon}</span>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">{type.title}</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6">
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">{type.desc}</p>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-3 mb-3">
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">When Courts Award This:</p>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">{type.when}</p>
              </div>
              <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 italic">{type.note}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Best Interests Standard -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-3">The Best-Interests Standard</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Maryland courts weigh a comprehensive set of factors to determine what custody arrangement best serves the child's wellbeing. Understanding these factors is essential to building your case.</p>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        {[
          "Fitness of each parent as a parent",
          "Character and reputation of each parent",
          "Desire of the parents and any agreements",
          "Ability to maintain relationship with the other parent",
          "Material opportunities available",
          "Age, health, and sex of the child",
          "Residences of parents and opportunities for visitation",
          "Length of separation of the parties",
          "Prior voluntary abandonment or surrender of custody",
          "Preference of the child (depending on age and maturity)",
          "Material changes in circumstance since any prior order",
          "Any other relevant factor the court deems appropriate"
        ].map((factor, i) => (
          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4 border border-gray-100 flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-[#D4A843] font-bold text-sm w-5 flex-shrink-0">{i + 1}.</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 text-sm">{factor}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Parenting Plans -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#0D6E6E]">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="text-white">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-5">Comprehensive Parenting Plans</h2>
          <p class="text-white/80 mb-4">
            A well-crafted parenting plan is the foundation of a successful co-parenting arrangement. Maryland courts look favorably on parents who submit detailed, thoughtful plans that demonstrate they've considered their children's needs carefully.
          </p>
          <p class="text-white/80 mb-4">
            Generic plans lead to future disputes. We draft comprehensive, specific parenting plans that address every contingency — leaving as little room as possible for future conflict.
          </p>
          <a href="/free-consultation" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-[#D4A843] text-white font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#b8902f] transition-colors mt-2">
            Get Help with Your Parenting Plan
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-3">What a Strong Parenting Plan Covers:</h3>
          {[
            { section: "Regular Schedule", items: ["Weekday and weekend rotation", "Pickup/dropoff logistics and responsibility"] },
            { section: "Holidays & Special Days", items: ["Holiday schedule and rotation rules", "Birthdays, school events, and vacations"] },
            { section: "Communication", items: ["Parent-to-parent communication protocols", "Child's right to contact both parents"] },
            { section: "Decision-Making", items: ["How major decisions are made jointly", "Tie-breaking procedures for disagreements"] },
            { section: "Modification Triggers", items: ["When the plan can be revisited", "School change, relocation, schedule changes"] }
          ].map(section => (
            <div class="bg-white/10 rounded-lg p-4 text-white">
              <p class="font-bold text-[#D4A843] text-sm">{section.section}</p>
              <ul class="mt-1 space-y-1">
                {section.items.map(item => (
                  <li class="text-white/80 text-xs flex items-center gap-2">
                    <span class="text-[#D4A843]">•</span>
                    {item}
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Special Situations -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 text-center mb-12">Complex Custody Situations We Handle</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {[
          {
            title: "High-Conflict Custody",
            desc: "When communication breaks down completely, we pursue structured arrangements with detailed parenting plans and, when needed, seek court intervention to protect your children and your rights."
          },
          {
            title: "Relocation Disputes",
            desc: "A parent seeking to move out of state must provide notice and obtain court approval or consent. We represent parents both seeking to relocate and opposing relocation requests."
          },
          {
            title: "Domestic Violence Cases",
            desc: "Safety comes first. We help victims secure protective orders, supervised visitation, and custody arrangements that protect children from exposure to domestic violence."
          },
          {
            title: "Alienation & Interference",
            desc: "Parental alienation — when one parent undermines the child's relationship with the other — is taken seriously by Maryland courts. We document and present this evidence effectively."
          },
          {
            title: "Third-Party & Grandparent Custody",
            desc: "In certain circumstances, grandparents or other third parties may seek custody or visitation. Our attorneys have fiercely advocated in contested de facto and third-party custody cases."
          },
          {
            title: "Interstate Custody (UCCJEA)",
            desc: "When parents live in different states, jurisdiction questions arise under the Uniform Child Custody Jurisdiction and Enforcement Act. We navigate these complex multi-state issues."
          }
        ].map(situation => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-100">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#0D6E6E] mb-2">{situation.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">{situation.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Modification CTA -->
  <section class="py-10 bg-white border-y border-gray-100">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-200">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">Need to Modify an Existing Custody Order?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-1">If circumstances have significantly changed since your order was entered, you may have grounds for modification.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/child-custody-modification" class="flex-shrink-0 bg-[#0D6E6E] text-white font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#0a5a5a] transition-colors">
          Learn About Modification →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Your Children Deserve the Best Representation</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Schedule a free consultation with one of our Maryland child custody attorneys. We'll help you understand your options and build a strategy centered on your children's best interests.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/free-consultation" class="bg-[#0D6E6E] text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#0a5a5a] transition-colors">
          Book Free Consultation
        </a>
        <a href="tel:3012898917" class="bg-[#D4A843] text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#b8902f] transition-colors">
          Call (301) 289-8917
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-4">Rockville: 100 Park Ave Suite 205 · Baltimore: 1537 Light St #100 · Mon–Fri 9AM–9PM</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
